			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-436135">
									

<p><em>Kudzu</em> is invasive and reproduces rapidly, and right now, this entry just says herbivores <em>avoid</em> the plants - there are plenty of natural ways for plants to repel things that would otherwise eat them (foul smells, bad taste, irritants, etc.).</p>
<p>If it's some kind of freaky repellent method that needs to be hidden from the public or if it exerts mind control or something, than I could understand the Foundation being involved. Otherwise, this is just a regular transgenic plant, and there are already <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transgenic_plant#Regulation_of_transgenic_plants">federal agencies that handle that sort of thing</a>, specifically the EPA, the FDA, and the USDA Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service.</p>

